      <h3>Anatomy of the Heart</h3>
      <p>The heart has four chambers: two upper atria and two lower ventricles. It's located in the thoracic cavity between the lungs and is about the size of a closed fist.</p>
      
      <h3>Key Functions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Blood Circulation:</strong> Pumps approximately 5 liters of blood throughout the body every minute.</li>
        <li><strong>Oxygen Delivery:</strong> Transports oxygenated blood from lungs to body tissues.</li>
        <li><strong>Nutrient Transport:</strong> Delivers essential nutrients to cells.</li>
        <li><strong>Waste Removal:</strong> Carries metabolic waste products to excretory organs.</li>
        <li><strong>Hormone Distribution:</strong> Helps transport hormones to target organs.</li>
      </ul>
      
